race.comment: Tricky race. INVINCIBLE WOMAN (4) is interesting first up off a spell. She won very well on debut at Caulfield Heath in a rich race before struggling badly when in the market in the Magic Millions 2yo Classic. She's won a jumpout leading in and gets Damian Lane aboard which is a good sign. Tipping she can be sharper than SONOFKIRK (1) over 1000m. He's a talented colt who will find this much easier than the G3 McNeil Stakes at Caulfield last time out but he does get back in the field and that's fraught with danger over the Moonee Valley 1000m. CAVALRY GIRL (2) was good at big odds behind My Gladiola two back which is great form and then did enough at Mornington as favourite. She can go on with it. BOLD SECRET (5) resumes having run a strong race on debut at Flemington last time in. He'll be hard to hold out late. SISSTAINABLE (6) is a sharp filly suited at 1000m.
